cs.NI, cs.SD, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.IT 

The paper discusses the challenges of Networked Music Performance (NMP) systems, which involve both audio and network components. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes an integration of dynamic audio and network configuration, which involves the use of Software Defined Networking (SDN) principles, making cs.SD (Systems and Control) another likely category. The paper also discusses the audio processing and transmission patterns, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). The proposed approach involves the interaction between the application and the network, which can be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
